						<summary>

						<p>The inscription gives the exact day of the transaction as 214 of the regnal year. It is damaged. Mention is made of a theft of the golden bowl and a fillet from the temple and of their replacement, after recovering their cost(?) from those who were probably responsible for it (by negligence).</p>						

